<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-37-0897 </DOCNO><TEXT>The confirmed world natural gas reserve is presently 103 billion m{sup3} which is equivalent to that of oil, and the ultimate reserve is saidto be 300 billion m{sup 3}. Japan ranks 6th in the world in the amountof natural gas consumption. The circumstances of natural gas usage inJapan differ very much from those in other countries. History of introductionof LNG is reported. To increase the use of LNG by the city gas industryin the future, it is necessary to improve the cost of LNG so that itmay be competitive enough with other kinds of energies. LNG projectsare guaranteed with long term stable supply, but lacks in flexibilityagainst the fluctuation in the demand. Major factors for the expansionof LNG business in the future are rationalization of cost and the pricelevel of oil. (6 figs, 14 tabs, 4 refs)</TEXT></DOC>